MISCELLANEOUS DISMISSALS

98-1733. State ex rel. Licking Cty. v. Licking Mem. Hosp.

This cause originated in this court on the filing of a complaint for a writ of mandamus. Upon consideration of the applications for dismissal of The Advocate and Licking County, Ohio,

IT IS ORDERED by the court that the applications for dismissal be, and hereby are, granted.

ACCORDINGLY, IT IS FURTHER ORDERED by the court that this cause be, and hereby is, dismissed.
